snippet doc_func
abbr	doc_func
	r"""${1:A one line description of the function}

	${2:Extended description of the function.}

	Parameters
	----------
	${3:var1} : ${4:array_like and type}
		${5:Description of the variable}

	Returns
	-------
	${6:describe} : ${7:type}
		${8:Explanation of return value named describe}

	Other Parameters
	----------------
	${9:only_seldom_used_keywords} : ${10:type}
		${11:Explanation of this parameter}

	Raises
	------
	${12:BadException}
		Because you shouldn't have done that.

	See Also
	--------
        other_func: Other function that this one might call

	Notes
	-----
	You may include some math:

	.. math:: X(e^{j\omega } ) = x(n)e^{ - j\omega n}

	Author
	------
	Shankar Kulumani		GWU		skulumani@gwu.edu

	References
	----------
	Cite the relevant literature, e.g. [1]_.  You may also cite these
	references in the notes section above.

	.. [1] Shannon, Claude E. "Communication theory of secrecy systems."
	Bell Labs Technical Journal 28.4 (1949): 656-715

	Examples
	--------
	An example of how to use the function

	>>> a = [1, 2, 3]
	>>> print [x + 3 for x in a]
	[4, 5, 6]
	>>> print "a\n\nb"
	a
	b

	"""${0}

